Forked from the scripts used in ArchiveTeam's Warrior. This is intended to be somewhat of a middle ground between the Warrior and the run-pipeline scripts.

usage: run-autorunner [-h] [--dir DIRECTORY] [--port PORT]
                      [--disable-web-server] [--address HOST] [--concurrent N]
                      DOWNLOADER

Run Archive Team's choice.

positional arguments:
  DOWNLOADER            your username

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --dir DIRECTORY       directory for data and projects
  --port PORT           the port number for the web interface (default: 8001)
  --disable-web-server  disable the web interface
  --address HOST        the IP address of the web interface (default: 0.0.0.0)
  --concurrent N        work on N items at a time (default: 1)

